	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Aug 7th 12:44 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Greetings, all!<br><br>I have a lvl 13 DE Enchanter and since my spouse and I finally have two accounts (to play together, that is), I am thinking to have him start a DE character (or a character who starts in Freeport) so that I can help him level up to where I am and we can hunt together.<br>That said, I have no idea what the best class to partner with an enchanter would be. He doesn't really like to use spells, so I wondered about warrior, but he started a warrior to play with my cleric, and I don't think he feels like playing two of the same class. He does also play a Pally (his preferred class, actually) so he probably wouldn't have an adversion to playing a class that uses some magic. However, he prefers...to put it in his words, to simply &quot;pound away at MoBs until they die a horrible death&quot;...<br>Any ideas? I'm interested in hearing THE best class to partner with an Enchanter as well as 2nd or 3rd best :)<br><br>Thanks!<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
