<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=103038834213288></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f103038834213288><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=13&mid=103038834213288>RE: Best Partner for Enchanter?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=13&mid=103038834213288#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=100200><span id= >Lphred</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>45 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Aug 26th 3:11 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.66]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Personally I say Shaman.&nbsp;&nbsp;Shaman gets Cann and Clarity, though I don't know if they stack, and have pets, like Necros.  They also have the DoTs and poisons.  Even though Chanters and Shaman are close to the same they are very good.  Chanter pulls with Tash, chanter pet aggros, Shaman sicks pet on, after 35 that is, shaman Malo, shaman DoT, chanter enfeeble chain stuns and occasionally nukes, watch as mob dies.  You still have to go to the store and everything, have no porter.  But if something happens the Shaman can heal, chanter can mez and mem blur.  It's not mabye the best but it is a good combo. <br>As you might have noticed I'm a Rogue and not a Chanter.  But I have seen this work well many times, just as I have seen Chanter/Necro.  I'd say chanter/necro or chanter/shaman.  <br>&nbsp;<br>Dangg Caronader<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=215560" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=215560</a> <br>51 Rogue <br>Shadowstormers, Karana</td></tr>
