	   <tr><td colspan=2>While i may agree with your sentiment Glass, in her original question, she did state that her partner doesn't like casting all that much, so at least in my case, that influenced my recommendations.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br><br>So far, i've had a good deal of luck pairing my enchanter with both wizards and druids.  After we've used Soothe or Harmony to prevent multiple pulls, i'll use a debuff to pull a single mob.  After it hits me, i back off and let my animation be my tank.  I'll then cast my array of debuffs and sit down to watch the fight.  <br><br>When i was partnered with a wizard, she'd unload a couple of nukes when the mob got below half, or if my pet was taking a beating.  With the druid, she'd snare and dot the mob, then toss one nuke when it hit half health.  Shortly after that, the mob would be in flight mode, and with the snare, would just stand there waiting to be wiped out.<br><br>Since pets heal at 10x our healing rate, he's at full strength before we're at full mana.  Which as you said, means no healing is needed.<br><br>Some day, i'd like to be in a group that consisted of two wizards, three mages, and an enchanter.  Five nuke throwers (two with critical blasts,) two elementals, a charmed mob, and someone passing out mind candy (clarity).  Don't you think that'd be fun to watch?<br>&nbsp;<br>Arjaizen Izrhume<br>38th Circle Wizard of Erudin<br>Fallen Wolves</td></tr>
